<dl id="s15027am"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us15" href="#s15027am">Circe: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s15all.htm#s15027am">sector 27(am)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> nose length of forehead / &mdash; width length of eye</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>A nose to be perfect should equal the length of the forehead</mark>; it may, when the forehead is exceptionally low, be even longer than the forehead (and in most of the beautiful antique statues it is so), but on no account should it be shorter than the brow. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Perhaps a better rule of proportion &mdash; as regards the whole face &mdash; is that the <mark>width of the nose between the eyes should be exactly the length of the eye</mark>. <small> Rosa Baughan, <a name="RBIS" href="/udra/udex.htm#rbis"><cite title="source">The Influence of the Stars</cite></a> (1891) 133</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
